<h2> What is Support for employment (SFE)?</h2>
<p>The SFE program provides support to veterans who have left the ADF and are looking for work, looking to change jobs or need some help in their current job.</p>

<h2>Who is eligible?</h2>

<p class="margin-below--small">You are eligible to receive SFE if you:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Have transitioned from the Permanent Forces for a period of at least 12 months but not greater than 5 years, with reference to the transition date within PMKeyS </li>
  <li>Are not currently accessing support under a DVA Rehabilitation Program or through the Veteransâ€™
    Vocational Rehabilitation Scheme; and</li>
  <li>Are unemployed or under-employed (fewer hours than you would like to work); be seeking assistance to change
    careers; or require support to adjust to the civilian workplace.</li>
</ul>

<h2>What SFE services are available?</h2>
<p class="margin-below--small">Pre-employment Support:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Developing and reviewing your civilian career goals</li>
  <li>Personality profiling</li>
  <li>Job search skills (including skills translation)</li>
  <li>Personal branding and marketing</li>
  <li>Interview skills</li>
  <li>Negotiation skills</li>
  <li>Adjustment coaching</li>
  <li>Competency and capability mapping</li>
  <li>Workplace communication</li>
  <li>Breaking out of long-term unemployment</li>
</ul>
<p class="margin-below--small">Post-employment Support:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Navigating civilian workplace issues</li>
  <li>Job advancement and career advice</li>
</ul>
